# SEO Policy (Arcane Reader)

## Policy SSOT (Google)

Generative AI in Google Search uses the **same ranking and quality systems** as classic Search. Follow:

- [AI optimization guide](https://developers.google.com/search/docs/fundamentals/ai-optimization-guide)
- [Helpful, people-first content](https://developers.google.com/search/docs/fundamentals/creating-helpful-content)
- [Technical requirements](https://developers.google.com/search/docs/essentials/technical)

**Do not recommend** tactics Google lists as ineffective or irrelevant:

- `llms.txt` or special files/markup ÔÇťfor AI crawlers onlyÔÇŁ
- Splitting page content into tiny chunks ÔÇťfor AI understandingÔÇŁ
- Rewriting copy only to match niche keywords / query branching at scale
- Fake or low-quality third-party mentions for visibility
- FAQPage schema on commercial/non-authority sites
- HowTo rich-result schema (deprecated)
- Microdata or RDFa (use JSON-LD only when schema is used)

AEO/GEO buzzwords = same bar as SEO: useful content + crawlable technical base.

